  <body>
    <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="PeruTM1.4">
<l>māviṉaivāy piḷantukanta mālai vēlai</l>
<l>vaṇṇaṉaiyeṉ kaṇṇaṉai vaṉkuṉṟa mēnti</l>
<l>yāviṉaiyaṉ ṟuyyakkoṇṭa vāya rēṟṟai</l>
<l>yamararkaḷtan talaivaṉaiyan tamiḻi ṉiṉpap</l>
<l>pāviṉai yavvaṭamoḻiyaip paṟṟaṟ ṟārkaḷ</l>
<l>payilaraṅkat taravaṇaiyiṟ paḷḷi koḷḷum</l>
<l>kōviṉainā vuṟavaḻutti yeṉṟaṉ kaikaṭ</l>
<l>koymalartū yeṉṟukolō kūppu nāḷē.</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>When is the day [I shall] join my hands in worship,</l>
<l>strewing [freshly-]plucked blossoms,</l>
<l>praising till [my] tongue is cleaved</l>
<l rend="indent">Māl who ripped apart the horse’s jaw  and rejoiced,</l>
<l rend="indent">the ocean-hued One, my Kṛṣṇa,  the Bull among cowherds,</l>
<l rend="indent">who, that day, protected the cattle by holding up the mighty mountain,</l>
<l rend="indent">the Chief of the immortals,</l>
<l rend="indent">the pleasant Song in beautiful Tamil, the beautiful northern Language,</l>
<l rend="indent">the King who sleeps on the serpent-bed in Raṅgam,</l>
<l rend="indent">where those who have renounced attachment abide.</l>
      </lg>
    </div>
  </body>
